Some corrections and additions:
The DES only manages 22.5Mbit/sec, but you can use several chips parallel
to increase speed.
The DES is delivered as 48 Pin Plastic DIL or 68 Pin PLCC (just 48 pins
connected), the RSA as 100 Pin QFP.

The RSA handles primiality testing, RSA key generation, modulo calculation,
multiplication etc., programmed by 11 internal commands (cool!).
The DES stores 4 keys at one time and keeps all sensitive information inside.

Both chips are addressed via registers.

The DES' databus is programmable for 8, 16 and 32 bit-mode.

Hoping to help you,

Kurt

